                    {% include 'icons/party' icon_class: 'block mx-auto' %}
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
    <div  class="mt-12 lg:mt-24 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 md:gap-8 lg:gap-12">
        <h3 class="mb-8 text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold uppercase">So feel free to pull a chair and go <span
            class="normal-case">LoCo</span>
          with us</h3>
        <div class="md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-3 text-lg space-y-6">
          <p>We’ve spent the last 25+ years combined in the outdoor cooking industry, but we cut our teeth (literally)
            on
            rib bones and ice-cold pull-top cans on the porch with family and friends. If there’s one thing that rings
            in
            our ears from childhood, it’s the voices of our grandparents, aunts, uncles, neighbors and friends saying,
            “Pull up a chair and take a seat.” Our best memories, toughest lessons, favorite stories and secret recipes
            were discovered sitting around tables. Based solely on our experiences, we believe inviting somebody to pull
            up a chair might just be the simplest way to make the world a better place…and that is something we can all
            do.</p>
          <p>We’re simple people from East Texas and South Alabama who appreciate the finer things in life. In
            everything
